"nathcooking"  "comment_text": "Pour un cercle à tarte de 20x3 5 cm
Pâte sucrée
180g de farine (de préférence type 55)
100g de beurre mou
65g de sucre en poudre
20g de poudre d’amandes
35g d’oeuf
1 pincée de sel

Crème d’amande aux abricots
70g de beurre pommade
70g de sucre en poudre
70g de poudre d’amandes
70g d’œuf
Quartiers d’abricots

Compotée d’abricots
250g d’abricots dénoyautés
2 5g de pectine NH
60g de sucre en poudre

Ganache montée vanille
80g de crème liquide entière(1)
60g de chocolat blanc
120g de crème liquide entière froide (2)
1 gousse de vanille
1g de gélatine réhydratée dans 6g d’eau froide(ou 1/2 feuille réhydratée dans un bol d’eau froide et bien essorée)

Abricots frais pour la garniture
Suite⬇️⬇️⬇️"}  "35": {"comment_id": "nathcooking"  "comment_text": "@nathcooking Pour la ganache montée vanille(à faire la veille):
Mettre le chocolat blanc dans le bol du Thermomix et hacher 5 sec/vitesse 8.
Ajouter la crème liquide(1) et les grains de la gousse de vanille et chauffer 3 min/98°C/vitesse 2.
Ajouter la gélatine réhydratée et mélanger 20 sec/vitesse 6.
Ajouter la crème liquide froide(2)et mélanger 20 sec/vitesse 5.
Débarrasser dans un saladier filmer au contact et mettre au frigo pour une nuit.

Pour la pâte sucrée(peut se faire la veille):
Mettre le sucre en poudre dans le bol et pulvériser 15sec/vit9.
Racler les parois du bol avec la spatule.
Ajouter le beurre coupé en morceaux la poudre d’amandes une pincée de sel et mélanger 1 min/vitesse 3.
Ajouter l’œuf et mélanger 30 sec/vitesse 4.
Ajouter la farine et pétrir 1 min/mode pétrin.
Former une boule et l’étaler grossièrement entre deux feuilles de papier cuisson.
Réserver au frigo au moins 2 heures(ou toute une nuit).
Foncer un cercle à tarte avec la pâte et réserver au congélateur une trentaine de minutes.

Pour la crème d’amande aux abricots(peut se faire la veille):
Mettre tous les ingrédients de la crème d’amande dans le bol(sauf les abricots)et mélanger 1 min/vitesse 5.

Pour la compotée d’abricots (à faire le jour j):
Mettre les abricots et 30 g de sucre dans le bol et mixer 10 sec/vitesse 6.
Racler les parois du bol avec la spatule.
Chauffer 3 min/37°C/vitesse 1.
Ajouter la pectine préalablement mélangée à 30 g de sucre et chauffer 3 min/100°C/vitesse 3.
Mélanger 20 sec/vitesse 6.
Laisser refroidir jusqu’à ce que la compotée est bien épaissi.
Suite⬇️⬇️⬇️"}  "36": {"comment_id": "nathcooking"  "comment_text": "@nathcooking Montage:
Préchauffer le four à 170°C.
Garnir le fond de tarte avec la crème d’amande et déposer quelques quartiers d’abricots sur le dessus.
Enfourner 35 minutes environ.
Il est possible de décercler le fond de tarte au bout de 20/22 minutes de dorer les côtés avec un mélange jaune d’œuf/crème liquide(1 jaune mélangé à 5g de crème)et de poursuivre la cuisson.
Laisser refroidir.
Verser la compotée d’abricots sur le fond de tarte.
Insérer le fouet dans le bol propre.
Mettre la ganache et fouetter entre 30 sec-3 min/vitesse 3(ou à l’aide d’un batteur monter la ganache comme une chantilly).
La ganache est prête lorsqu’elle tient sur le fouet(à surveiller de près).
Pocher ensuite la ganache sur la tarte et garnir de quartiers d’abricots.
Si vous utilisez un cercle à tarte avec une hauteur de 2 cm  il faudra diminuer un peu la quantité de crème d’amande et de compotée d’abricots."}}

main_text: Die Wachau umfasst die Flusslandschaft im rund 35 km langen östlichen (unteren) zwischen Melk und Krems an der Donau[3] gelegenen Südwest-Nordost verlaufenden Abschnitt eines Durchbruchstals der Donau einschließlich des Seitentals Spitzer Graben sowie die jeweils angrenzenden Hochlagen. Die Donau schneidet sich hier wie auch im westlich (flussaufwärts) benachbarten Struden- und Nibelungengau durch die Südspitze der Böhmischen Masse. Die Wachau gehört demzufolge zur südlichen Randzone des österreichischen Naturraums Granit- und Gneishochland. Die höchsten Erhebungen sind der Jauerling (960 m ü. A.) und Sandl (723 m).📸@wachau_photo

main_text: Wednesday brings apricot roses and a baby fledged blackbird whose mama brought him to my window to feed. I’m a constant voice in the lives of all babies who nest near my office window- it started during lockdown and now seems to be a pattern. The babies often arrive on their first flight and sit by me and chat away peering through the glass as they wobble precariously. It’s a moment I wait for each year now and it’s very precious. main_text: Aprikosen-Kokos Tarte 🍑🥥🥧 um Mal ein bisschen Abwechslung in euren Feed zu bringen der vermutlich von Erdbeertorten und Spargelrezepten dominiert wird.😉Aber die kunterbunte Früchtesaison beginnt ja gerade. Heute also Mal die Farbe orange 🧡~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ZUTATENFür den Teig:🍑250g helles Mehl🍑125g Butter🍑100g Zucker🍑1 Päckchen Vanillezucker🍑1 Ei🍑1 Prise Salz.Für die Füllung:🍑300g Aprikosenmarmelade🍑20g Kokosraspeln🍑4 EL Batida de Coco.Außerdem:🍑1 Eigelb🍑2 EL Milch.ZUBEREITUNG🥥 Das Mehl mit kalter Butter Zucker Vanillezucker Ei und Salz in einer Schüssel miteinander zu einem glatten Teig verkneten 🥥 Den Teil in Folie wickeln und 30 Minuten in den Kühlschrank legen🥥Eine Tarteform (oder Springform) einfetten und den Boden und den Rand mit 2/3 des Teiges auskleiden🥥 Aus dem restlichen Teig 10 dünne Rollen formen🥥die Marmelade mit Batida de Coco glatt rühren und in der Form verstreichen🥥mit Kokosraspeln bestreuen und die Teigrollen gitterformig darüber legen🥥Das Eigelb mit Milch verquirlen und den Teig damit bestreichen🥥die Tarte bei 210 Grad ca. 30 Minuten backen.#aprikosentarte #kokos #kuchen #backen #sommerkuchen #aprikosen #apricot #kuchenliebe #backen #tarte #sonntagskuchen #backenmitliebe #selbstgemachterkuchen #batidadecoo #kokosrezept #aprikosenkuchen #marmelade
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "annas_kuestenkueche"  "comment_text": "Aprikosen-Kokos Tarte 🍑🥥🥧 um Mal ein bisschen Abwechslung in euren Feed zu bringen  der vermutlich von Erdbeertorten und Spargelrezepten dominiert wird.😉
Aber die kunterbunte Früchtesaison beginnt ja gerade. Heute also Mal die Farbe orange 🧡
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
ZUTATEN
Für den Teig:
🍑250g helles Mehl
🍑125g Butter
🍑100g Zucker
🍑1 Päckchen Vanillezucker
🍑1 Ei
🍑1 Prise Salz
.
Für die Füllung:
🍑300g Aprikosenmarmelade
🍑20g Kokosraspeln
🍑4 EL Batida de Coco
.
Außerdem:
🍑1 Eigelb
🍑2 EL Milch
.
ZUBEREITUNG
🥥 Das Mehl mit kalter Butter  Zucker  Vanillezucker  Ei und Salz in einer Schüssel miteinander zu einem glatten Teig verkneten 🥥 Den Teil in Folie wickeln und 30 Minuten in den Kühlschrank legen
🥥Eine Tarteform (oder Springform) einfetten und den Boden und den Rand mit 2/3 des Teiges auskleiden
🥥 Aus dem restlichen Teig 10 dünne Rollen formen
🥥die Marmelade mit Batida de Coco glatt rühren und in der Form verstreichen
🥥mit Kokosraspeln bestreuen und die Teigrollen gitterformig darüber legen
🥥Das Eigelb mit Milch verquirlen und den Teig damit bestreichen
🥥die Tarte bei 210 Grad ca. 30 Minuten backen
.

main_text: BEETS apricot cheese.No meeting nights tend to end with a good dinner plate :)Inspired by the grilled and dried beet dish @sonsanddaughterssf (chef @jwesley___ ) here is my attempt at the recreation.The original dish was served with bone marrow sauce and preserved huckleberries. The texture of the beet was very candy like but with a good bite to it that I loved.And when you don’t have access to bone marrow and huckleberries you make do with what you find at home :)I tried to recreate the beet texture (wild guesses and over engineering at play!) by soaking the beets in calcium hydroxide curing grilling and then dehydrating the beets (very different from the technique used at the restaurant). I had to tweak it a bit to reduce the crunch (caused by the pickling lime).Served with whipped goat cheese and preserved apricots (with bergamot and ginger) topped with apricot kernel and drizzle of tarragon oil.Was the texture close to what I tasted? Well not there yet. But pretty happy for a first try. I know what to change for next time!#finefood #finedining #foodplating #artofplating #platingfood #InstaFood #Foodstagram #foodstyling #foodnerd #PerfectlyPlated #finediningathome #foodnerd #madefromscratch #homecook #chefsofinstagram #finefoodofinstagram #finedininglovers #homecooking #foodart #beets #beetroot #apricot #goatcheese #tarragon #grilledbeets #dinnerscenes
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "tad.bit.sweet"  "comment_text": "BEETS  apricot  cheese.

No meeting nights tend to end with a good dinner plate :)

Inspired by the grilled and dried beet dish @sonsanddaughterssf (chef @jwesley___ )  here is my attempt at the recreation.
The original dish was served with bone marrow sauce and preserved huckleberries. The texture of the beet was very candy like but with a good bite to it  that I loved.
And when you don’t have access to bone marrow and huckleberries  you make do with what you find at home :)

I tried to recreate the beet texture (wild guesses and over engineering at play!) by soaking the beets in calcium hydroxide  curing  grilling and then dehydrating the beets (very different from the technique used at the restaurant). I had to tweak it a bit to reduce the crunch (caused by the pickling lime).

Served with whipped goat cheese and preserved apricots (with bergamot and ginger)  topped with apricot kernel and drizzle of tarragon oil.

Was the texture close to what I tasted? Well  not there yet. But pretty happy for a first try. I know what to change for next time!

The Golden Broken RecordMy submission for #giffardwestcup2022Worthy Park Single Estate RumGiffard Apricot LiqueurGiffard Espelette Pepper LiqueurFresh Lime JuiceAromatic Mist*My song choice Do It Again by Steely Dan was trailblazing in the direction for this competition. It's a song I've been quite fond of for many years in fact the album in which it is featured on celebrates 50 years!A good sign so far.The essence of the song is very tropical the rhythm section and keyboards bring you feelings of warmth while you sway to the beat. So my selection of Worthy Park Rum drawing influence from the classic Daiquiri nearly felt intrinsic.The flavors were beginning to speak to me.This was my first time using either Giffard's Apricot & Espelette Pepper Liqueur but I felt they would play well with the direction I wanted to take this drink.It's almost rather fitting seeing as how the song itself is a debut for the band and these two flavors are newly being used in my arsenal both very introductory in a sense.The warmth of the apricot blends with the rum and sound of the song almost electrically when I close my eyes and listen I see golden lights dancing and shimmering about. Each of these incorporated colors and choice flavors are golden in their own shade.The Espelette Pepper brings the heat which lyrically is drawing literal inspiration from the songs protagonist "Jack" getting into trouble. Whether it be the law relationships over and over finding themself in heated situations. Almost like a broken record skipping over itself. Hence the name. The Golden Broken Record.*mist* - build a .25 part of absinthe then 6 dashes of orange bitters (used Ragens no. 6) and 2 drops of chocolate bitters (used Bittermens Xocolate Mole) into an atomizer for your mist to spray over the cocktail once finished.(I wanted to keep this drink simple in essence of whats going into the shaker yet bring some creativity with this aromatic for the drink. They specifically comliment the flavors of both Giffard products the Apricot and Pepper liqueurs)@giffard_liqueurs_syrups@giffardusa@worthyparkestate@backbarlauren@backbarproject
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "barbourgeois"  "comment_text": "The Golden Broken Record

My submission for #giffardwestcup2022

Worthy Park Single Estate Rum
Giffard Apricot Liqueur
Giffard Espelette Pepper Liqueur
Fresh Lime Juice
Aromatic Mist*

My song choice  Do It Again by Steely Dan  was trailblazing in the direction for this competition. It's a song I've been quite fond of for many years  in fact the album in which it is featured on celebrates 50 years!

A good sign so far.

The essence of the song is very tropical  the rhythm section and keyboards bring you feelings of warmth while you sway to the beat. So my selection of Worthy Park Rum  drawing influence from the classic Daiquiri  nearly felt intrinsic.

The flavors were beginning to speak to me.

This was my first time using either Giffard's Apricot & Espelette Pepper Liqueur  but I felt they would play well with the direction I wanted to take this drink.

It's almost rather fitting seeing as how the song itself is a debut for the band  and these two flavors are newly being used in my arsenal  both very introductory in a sense.

The warmth of the apricot blends with the rum and sound of the song almost electrically  when I close my eyes and listen  I see golden lights dancing and shimmering about. Each of these incorporated colors and choice flavors are golden in their own shade.

The Espelette Pepper brings the heat  which lyrically is drawing literal inspiration from the songs protagonist "Jack" getting into trouble. Whether it be the law  relationships  over and over finding themself in heated situations. Almost like a broken record  skipping over itself. Hence the name. The Golden Broken Record.

*mist* - build a .25 part of absinthe  then 6 dashes of orange bitters (used Ragens no. 6)  and 2 drops of chocolate bitters (used Bittermens Xocolate Mole) into an atomizer for your mist to spray over the cocktail once finished.

(I wanted to keep this drink simple in essence of whats going into the shaker  yet bring some creativity with this aromatic for the drink. They specifically comliment the flavors of both Giffard products  the Apricot and Pepper liqueurs)

main_text: Don't Buy this Fruit at a Grocery Store. Stone fruits (cherries excluded) are one of the fruits I generally avoid purchasing at a grocery store. In most cases the fruit is picked too early and may have chill damage so it will never properly ripen get sweet or have a juicy texture. Store bought apricots are often insipid unsweet and mealy. I encourage you to pick your own stone fruit to eat. Of couse the best way is to grow fruit trees yourself but if you are unable visit a local farm like I did today and pick your own fruit right off their trees so now you are in control of the ripeness and get the ripest fruit to eat. If you don't have a you pick farm then the next best is buying direct from the farmers market where fruit is often riper than the grocery store. I encourage you to support small farmers as most industrially grown food is grown by corporations. I am grateful that I have farms near me so I can eat riper fruit than most Americans eat. #apricots #apricotfruit #apricot #youpickfarm #gilcreaseorchard #fruit #freshfruit #pickingfruit #fruitpicker #freshapricots #stonefruit #stonefruitseason #growingyourgreens #rawvegan #fruit #fruiteater #nutrientdense #nutritarian
